    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-04-05T20:41:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-04-05T20:41:00-05:00" n="236"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d236">
                <head>236. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Syria</gloss>
                    <note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d236fn0">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 783.00/4–562. Secret; Priority. Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_BJR2">Barrow</persName>; cleared by <persName
                            corresp="#p_SRC4">Strong</persName>, Hewitt, <persName
                            corresp="#p_MGGC2">McGhee</persName>, Veliotes, Moser (E), <persName
                            corresp="#p_IWC1">Ide</persName> and Anderson (<gloss target="#t_AID1"
                            >AID</gloss>), Welk (ExImBank) informed, and <persName corresp="#p_TPH2"
                            >Talbot</persName>; and approved by <persName corresp="#p_BGW1"
                            >Ball</persName>. Repeated to Amman, Ankara, Baghdad, Beirut, Bonn,
                        Cairo, Jidda, London, Paris, Rome, Tel Aviv, Kuwait, and Taiz.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1962-04-05T20:41:00-05:00">April 5, 1962, 8:41 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>438. Provided and at such time as Qudsi reinstated as President and
                    reconstitution of government being undertaken, and provided you convinced
                    General Command has de facto control of Syria and <gloss target="#t_SARG1"
                        >SARG</gloss> prepared adhere to its international obligations, you
                    authorized in your discretion and at time you deem most appropriate, to resume
                    normal relations with <gloss target="#t_SARG1">SARG</gloss>. In name of USG you
                    may assure <gloss target="#t_SARG1">SARG</gloss> of our every good wish for
                    success Syrian Government and people. You might at same time state USG will
                    abide by existing economic assistance commitments, and is prepared discuss
                    completion of US component stabilization package under same conditions as agreed
                    upon earlier.</p>
                <p>If asked whether this constitutes recognition, you may state in our opinion
                    formal act of recognition not required unless <gloss target="#t_SARG1"
                        >SARG</gloss> requests it.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>: We hope prompt action along these lines
                    might help counteract <gloss target="#t_SARG1">SARG</gloss> erroneous impression
                    USG favors <gloss target="#t_UAR1">UAR</gloss> control of Syria and establish
                    favorable basis US relations new government. End <gloss target="#t_FYI1"
                        >FYI</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Embassy London may inform <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> re foregoing
                    instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BGW1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Ball</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
